underlying_goal: To commit recent changes to the git repository with logical, well-formatted commit messages.
primary_success: Correctly analyzed the git status, logically separated the changes into two distinct commits, wrote clear commit messages for each, and correctly excluded untracked/generated files.
brief_summary: The user initiated a commit workflow. Claude analyzed the modified files, intelligently split them into two logical commits (one for refactoring Week 19 slides, one for adding new Week 20 slides), wrote appropriate messages, and executed the commits. It also correctly ignored untracked files and warned the user before offering to push to the main branch.
